These injected electrons are transported between TiO2 nanoparticles and diffuse towards the back contact (transparent conducting oxide [TCO]). Through the external circuit, electrons reach at the counter electrode.
The electrons at the counter electrode reduce I− 3 to I−; thus, dye regeneration or the regeneration of the ground state of the dye takes place due to the acceptance of electrons from I− ion redox mediator, and I− gets oxidized to I− 3 (oxidized state).S+/S∗+e−➔S+/S\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
